 always made use of images to spread their cause through the media – as have their enemy, the state. This is an indispensable book for understanding the background and dynamic of terror today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPropagandaxHistory. 0aTerrorism and mass mediaxHistory. 0aTerrorismxHistory. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Terrorism.2bisacsh  abomb attacks.  ahistory of terror.  ahostage-taking.  aimage patterns.  aimage strategies.  amedia frames.  amedia icons.  apropaganda.  asocial media.  aterror.1 aKlonk, Charlotte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614931240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526149312423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526149312/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles